         <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-zinc-900 leading-none tracking-tight">Is ADHD a Disability Under the ADA?</h1>
         <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">The short answer is <strong class="text-accent-dark">yes</strong>. ADHD can qualify as a disability under the ADA when it substantially limits one or more major life activities. Here is how the law defines it and what protections you have.</p>
       </div>
